{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:hebrews.3",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "hebrews",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Hebrews 3 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:1",
      "text": "Wherefore, holy brethren, partakers of the heavenly calling, consider the Apostle and High Priest of our profession, Christ Jesus;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:2",
      "text": "Who was faithful to him that appointed him, as also Moses was faithful in all his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:3",
      "text": "For this man was counted worthy of more glory than Moses, inasmuch as he who hath builded the house hath more honour than the house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:4",
      "text": "For every house is builded by some man; but he that built all things is God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:5",
      "text": "And Moses verily was faithful in all his house, as a servant, for a testimony of those things which were to be spoken after;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:6",
      "text": "But Christ as a son over his own house; whose house are we, if we hold fast the confidence and the rejoicing of the hope firm unto the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:7",
      "text": "Wherefore (as the Holy Ghost saith, To day if ye will hear his voice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:8",
      "text": "Harden not your hearts, as in the provocation, in the day of temptation in the wilderness:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:9",
      "text": "When your fathers tempted me, proved me, and saw my works forty years.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:10",
      "text": "Wherefore I was grieved with that generation, and said, They do alway err in their heart; and they have not known my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:11",
      "text": "So I sware in my wrath, They shall not enter into my rest.)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:12",
      "text": "Take heed, brethren, lest there be in any of you an evil heart of unbelief, in departing from the living God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:13",
      "text": "But exhort one another daily, while it is called To day; lest any of you be hardened through the deceitfulness of sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:14",
      "text": "For we are made partakers of Christ, if we hold the beginning of our confidence stedfast unto the end;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:15",
      "text": "While it is said, To day if ye will hear his voice, harden not your hearts, as in the provocation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:16",
      "text": "For some, when they had heard, did provoke: howbeit not all that came out of Egypt by Moses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:17",
      "text": "But with whom was he grieved forty years? was it not with them that had sinned, whose carcases fell in the wilderness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:18",
      "text": "And to whom sware he that they should not enter into his rest, but to them that believed not?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:hebrews.3.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:19",
      "text": "So we see that they could not enter in because of unbelief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
